In addition to the goals [~epayne] listed, another goal is to make it easier for users to compare how code changes to a particular recurring Hadoop job affect its resource usage.  Assuming input data size didn't significantly change, It'd be much more apparent after to the user after a code change if there was a resulting significant change in the resource usage for their job.  Even without charging, I'm hoping that having the resource usage shown to the user, without any extra work on their part, will make more people think about their overall grid resource usage, instead of just run times.

